## 5. API Resource Specifications

### 5.1. The Provider Resource

**Endpoint:** `POST /v1/providers`
**Purpose:** Defines a single AI endpoint with its connection details and protocol adapter.

#### 5.1.1. Provider Schema

```json
{
  "id": "provider_openai_prod",
  "name": "OpenAI Production",
  "spec": {
    "type": "openai",
    "endpoint": "https://api.openai.com",
    
    "adapter": {
      // Authentication
      "auth": { 
        "type": "bearer", 
        "secret_ref": "vault://openai-key" 
      },

      // Header transformations
      "headers": {
        "add": { "OpenAI-Organization": "org-main" },
        "remove": []
      },

      // URL transformations
      "url": {
        "path_prefix": "/v1",
        "path_template": null,
        "query_params": {}
      },

      // Body transformations (request)
      "request_body": {
        "format": "openai_chat",  // canonical format this provider expects
        "field_mappings": {},     // custom field name mappings
        "defaults": {},           // default values to inject
        "remove_fields": []       // fields to strip before sending
      },

      // Body transformations (response)
      "response_body": {
        "format": "openai_chat",  // format of provider's response
        "field_mappings": {}      // map back to canonical format
      }
    },

    "connection_pool": {
      "max_size": 100,
      "min_idle": 10,
      "max_idle_timeout": "300s"
    }
  }
}
```

