#### 5.1.3. Body Transformation Formats

The gateway uses a **canonical format** (OpenAI-compatible) as the internal representation. Adapters transform to/from provider-specific formats.

**Canonical Request Format (OpenAI-compatible):**
```json
{
  "model": "gpt-4",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "system", "content": "..." },
    { "role": "user", "content": "..." }
  ],
  "temperature": 0.7,
  "top_p": 1.0,
  "max_tokens": 1000,
  "stream": true,
  "stop": ["END"],
  "presence_penalty": 0,
  "frequency_penalty": 0
}
```

**Provider Format Mappings:**

| Canonical Field | OpenAI | Anthropic | Google AI | AWS Bedrock (Claude) |
|----------------|--------|-----------|-----------|---------------------|
| `model` | `model` | `model` | `model` | (in URL path) |
| `messages` | `messages` | `messages` | `contents` | `messages` |
| `messages[].role` | `role` | `role` | `role` | `role` |
| `messages[].content` | `content` | `content` | `parts[].text` | `content` |
| `temperature` | `temperature` | `temperature` | `generationConfig.temperature` | `temperature` |
| `top_p` | `top_p` | `top_p` | `generationConfig.topP` | `top_p` |
| `max_tokens` | `max_tokens` | `max_tokens` | `generationConfig.maxOutputTokens` | `max_tokens` |
| `stream` | `stream` | `stream` | (SSE endpoint) | (invoke-with-response-stream) |
| `stop` | `stop` | `stop_sequences` | `generationConfig.stopSequences` | `stop_sequences` |

