## 10. Non-Functional Requirements

### 10.1. Performance Targets

| Metric | Target | Notes |
|--------|--------|-------|
| **Latency (p50)** | < 5ms added | Gateway overhead only, excludes upstream |
| **Latency (p99)** | < 20ms added | Under normal load |
| **Throughput** | 10,000 RPS per instance | Non-streaming requests |
| **Concurrent Connections** | 50,000 per instance | Across all tenants |
| **Config Update Latency** | < 100ms | Time from controller push to gateway apply |

### 10.2. Availability

- **Gateway SLA:** 99.9% availability
- **Graceful Degradation:** Continue serving with cached config if controller unavailable
- **Zero-Downtime Deploys:** Support rolling updates without dropped connections

### 10.3. Security

| Requirement | Implementation |
|-------------|----------------|
| **TLS Termination** | Required for all inbound traffic (TLS 1.2+) |
| **mTLS to Providers** | Optional, configurable per provider |
| **Secret Storage** | No plaintext secrets in config; reference external stores |
| **Input Validation** | Sanitize all user inputs; reject malformed requests |
| **Rate Limiting** | Prevent abuse with configurable limits |
| **Audit Logging** | Log all config changes with actor identity |

### 10.4. Scalability

- **Horizontal Scaling:** Add gateway instances behind load balancer
- **Multi-Region:** Support geo-distributed deployments with regional controllers
- **Tenant Isolation:** Resource quotas prevent noisy neighbor issues

