### E. Glossary

| Term | Definition |
|------|------------|
| **Control Plane** | The management layer (Controller + Database) that stores config and orchestrates gateways |
| **Data Plane** | The gateway instances that process actual traffic |
| **Provider** | A single AI endpoint with its connection details and protocol adapter |
| **Backend** | An orchestration layer grouping Providers with resilience policies |
| **Route** | A traffic entry point that matches requests and forwards to a Backend |
| **Adapter** | Protocol translation logic that transforms requests/responses for specific providers |
| **Body Transform** | JSON manipulation to convert between provider-specific formats |
| **Canonical Format** | The standardized request/response format (OpenAI-compatible) used internally |
| **Hot Reload** | Updating configuration without restarting the gateway process |
| **Circuit Breaker** | Pattern that stops sending requests to failing providers temporarily |
| **Radix Trie** | Data structure for efficient longest-prefix-match routing |
| **SSE** | Server-Sent Events, used for streaming AI responses |
| **Token** | Unit of text processing in LLMs (roughly 4 characters) |